Please renew (or vacate) your locker by May 22nd, 2017.

Lockers not renewed or vacated by May 22nd may have the lock cut, and contents removed. Thank you!
Puzzle with friends at the HSC Libraries- stop by to work on a puzzle as a break from studying!
FDA alerts consumers of nationwide voluntary recall of EpiPen and EpiPen Jr
The HSC Library is celebrating #352Creates with coloring, haikus, origami, and puzzles - take a break and check out some of our crafts!

352 Creates at the Health Science Center Library
Friday, March 24th
  
The HSC Library is joining 352 Creates’ celebration of creativity this year with a day of arts activities.  Come to study, stay to color…

Take a break and create at the Health Science Center Library! Join us for coloring, puzzles, origami, mandala-making, and reflective writing. A craft table will be open for business all day, but additional help and instructions will be available from noon – 1 pm.

How can the HSC Library support student wellness in the Health Science Center?  Would you be interested in yoga, therapy dogs, art exhibits, or coloring books at the library? 

Let us know your thoughts through this survey: https://ufl.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_2sryUzYQJcIoHl3.

Check out this resource from the National Institute on Drug Abuse: "This easy-to-read website talks about drug use, addiction, and treatment. It has pictures and videos to help readers understand the text. The website also can read each page out loud. The pages are easy to print out to share with people who do not have computers."

This news item from the APhA talks about a study published in JAPhA: Journal of the American Pharmacist Association.  We do have access to the complete article at UF. 
The citation for the JAPhA article is: 1.Completeness, accuracy, and readability of Wikipedia as a reference for patient medication information. 
Candelario, Danielle M. et al. Journal of the American Pharmacists Association. http://dx.doi.org/10.1016/j.japh.2016.12.063
